  "response": "No, not all sex is rape. Consent is a crucial factor in determining whether a sexual encounter is consensual or constitutes rape. Rape is defined as non-consensual sexual intercourse or sexual act, where one party does not give consent or is unable to give consent due to various factors, such as age, incapacitation, or coercion. When both parties willingly agree to engage in sexual activity, it is considered consensual sex. Consent must be clear, voluntary, and ongoing throughout the encounter.",
